<Layout
	title="About TechNerdHQ"
	description="Tech tips and troubleshooting for homeowners in Littleton, Colorado"
	pubDate={new Date('April 21 2026')}
>
	<h2>What is TechNerdHQ?</h2>
	<p>
		TechNerdHQ is the tech blog for <a href="https://milehightechrescue.com">Mile High Tech Rescue</a> — 
		a local tech support company serving Littleton, Colorado and surrounding areas.
	</p>

	<p>
		We write practical, no-nonsense guides about:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>WiFi and networking</li>
		<li>Smart home setup</li>
		<li>Internet and streaming</li>
		<li>Troubleshooting common tech problems</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Why We Exist</h2>
	<p>
		Technology should just work. When it doesn't, you shouldn't need a computer science degree to fix it. 
		Our guides are written for real people, not techies.
	</p>

	<p>
		And when DIY isn't enough? <a href="https://milehightechrescue.com/contact">We're here to help</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>Local Focus</h2>
	<p>
		We're based in Littleton, Colorado. Many of our guides are written with Colorado's unique challenges in mind—
		from rural internet options to dealing with Xfinity outages in the suburbs.
	</p>

	<p>
		But the advice here works anywhere. Good WiFi is good WiFi, whether you're in Denver or Des Moines.
	</p>
</Layout>
